    "In the following, the governing equations are briefly summarized.",
    "The Cauchy stress tensor in Eq. 1 consists of a hydrostatic term and a viscous term denoted as σ s: σ = -pI + σ s = -pI + 2ηε(u).",
    "Here, p is the pressure, η is the dynamic viscosity, and ε is the strain rate tensor ε(u) = 1 2 ∇u + ∇u T.",
    "For calculating the temperature T, we use the heat equation:",
    "with the thermal conductivity κ and the specific heat capacity c p."
